# NurseAda Authentication

## Provider

Supabase Auth with email + password. All clients share the same Supabase project.

## Backend (Gateway)

- JWT validation lives in `services/gateway/app/services/auth.py`.
- `get_current_user_optional` – returns `AuthUser | None`. Use for routes that work in guest mode (e.g. `/chat`).
- `require_auth` – returns `AuthUser` or 401. Use for routes that expose PHI (e.g. `/patient/{id}`).
- When `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET` is unset, auth is disabled (local dev). Guest requests proceed without a token.

## Client token injection

All API helpers (`lib/api.ts` on both web and mobile) accept an optional `token` parameter. Pass `accessToken` from the `useAuth()` context.

## Patient data access

- Patient ID fields in chat are only sent when the user is authenticated.
- The `/patient/{id}` route requires authentication; unauthenticated requests receive a clear 401 message.

## RLHF & PII

- The RLHF interaction hook records `has_user: bool` but never logs emails, names, or tokens.
- `user_id` from Supabase is an opaque UUID – safe to log.

## Error messages

Auth-related errors must be actionable and empathetic:

```
401: "Please sign in to access this feature."
401 (expired): "Your session has expired. Please sign in again."
503 (not configured): "Authentication is not configured on this server."
```

## Env vars

| Variable | Where | Purpose |
|----------|-------|---------|
| `SUPABASE_URL` | Gateway `.env` | Supabase project URL |
| `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Gateway `.env` | Supabase anon/public key |
| `SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET` | Gateway `.env` | JWT secret for token verification |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` | Web `.env.local` | Supabase URL (browser) |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Web `.env.local` | Supabase anon key (browser) |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` | Mobile `.env` | Supabase URL (Expo) |
| `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` | Mobile `.env` | Supabase anon key (Expo) |
